In case this is useful to others, this issue still occurs for functions written in old-style (pre-ISO) C with a declaration section *before* the function's opening bracket, like in this example [from Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indent_style#K.26R_style):

```c
/* Original pre-ISO C style without function prototypes */
int main(argc, argv)
    int   argc;
    char  *argv[];
{
    ...
}
```

