@yaron-idan sorry, I just noticed this issue now - it looks like the notification got lost in my email.

Before getting too deep into this, do you have any Reserved Instances? They don't count against the On-Demand Running Instances limits, so awslimitchecker subtracts the number of active reserved instances of each type in each AZ from the count of running instances of that type in that AZ. If that's not the issue:

Unfortunately, issues like this are really hard to reproduce. Do you think you could please run the script below and then ``awslimitchecker`` (with ``-vv`` as you did above) in the same virtualenv, one right after another, and then post the output? There shouldn't be any sensitive information in here, and it will at least give me enough to write a unit test for your case and dig into the problem.

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python

import boto3
import time
import json
import calendar

ec2 = boto3.resource('ec2')

data = {'ts': time.time(), 'instances': [], 'reservations': []}

for i in ec2.instances.all():
    info = {}
    for attr in ['id', 'instance_lifecycle', 'instance_type', 'placement',
                 'platform', 'spot_instance_request_id', 'state']:
        info[attr] = getattr(i, attr)
    info['launch_time'] = calendar.timegm(i.launch_time.timetuple())
    data['instances'].append(info)

client = boto3.client('ec2')
for r in client.describe_reserved_instances()['ReservedInstances']:
    info = {}
    for attr in ['State', 'ReservedInstancesId', 'AvailabilityZone',
                 'InstanceType', 'InstanceCount']:
        info[attr] = r[attr]
    data['reservations'].append(info)
print(json.dumps(data))
```

@timotheus I found root problem. Whole ebaysdk-python lib works with str by default. But as soon as someone would pass `unicode` to lib, everytime there is modulo operator it will change whole string to be unicode. And then everything collapse :/ So one way is to patch every incoming property and force it to be str. Or import unicode_literals in all lib. To be honest I don't know what is better here.

If you want to try this issue, just do `.execute(u'AddItem')` or something similar. 

Any thoughts? For now I think I will patch trading api for me, because we need it now, but I think the best solution here would be to switch to unicode strings everywhere.

