@lein Thank you for the patch!  Unfortunately, I'm going to have to vote -1 to this feature, because it breaks the fundamental TTW security model:

-  Editing a TTW script requires a different permission than changing its proxy roles:  The latter role is typically only granted to admin/manager users, and already has a dedicated UI.
- Filesystem-based scripts (e.g., in the CMF) have a different way to spell proxy roles.

